The first ones back to work

These days, Hangzhou's famous Xixi road is quiet. It is not only the headquarters of alipay, but also the home of start-ups large and small, dubbed the "old world overtime center. ". The old "Overtime Center" was brightly lit day and night, but now it was pitch black and there was no one there.

But the wall and his colleagues are an exception. They went into the venture capital center opposite the company, checked the admission certificate, temperature, neck masks, alcohol disinfection... Dozens of programmers without a word through the numerous checkpoints, into the second floor of the alipay temporary war room in extraordinary times.

The people behind the masks don't know each other. They come from alipay different departments, technology, products, operations, legal, customer service... The common task is in the shortest time, let the health code in Zhejiang Province on line.

Alipay is a senior technical experts, Health Code Project Technology No. 1 position, this 15-year-old Ali, experienced numerous stressful orderly major technical iterations, but this is the first time, "can only look at the next minute. ".

Since the outbreak of emergency, the Thor Mountain and fire God Mountain Star night construction, around the rapid build-up of medical teams, anti-epidemic war situation on the time limit is unprecedented. Now the country is about to usher in a wave of work around the return of people to form a new risk in the fight against the epidemic. In order to return to work safely and efficiently, on February 11, the day Hangzhou Health Code went online, Zhejiang asked the whole province to promote health code, and "immediately all over the province. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Previously, the first launch of the Hangzhou Yuhang District Health Code has been implemented for several days, the success of the traditional hand-written registration of the movement of people into the online punch card, the response is very good.

City Wall wanted to let everyone rest a few days, but then received on-line Zhejiang yards of the task, and is to concentrate on the attack under the line.

However, during the special period, most people are in the field, return to Hangzhou must first quarantine at home for 14 days, there is only one way to launch a 14-day stay in Hangzhou and healthy technical registration. At 2:00 a.m. , Jianqun pulled people to sign up. At 2:30 a.m. , the number of applicants reached dozens.

After entering the war room, Chengbi saw Fan Yu, a partner of Ali from a technical background. Fan Yu sat in the war room all night, mobilizing resources. More and more from Alibaba Cloud, nail's brother next door to join in the fight.

The temporary regiment worked round the clock, 24 hours a day, in double shifts. Hangzhou is still closed to the community, they have seen the 4:00 a.m. Xixi road.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A programmer on a camp bed

The "war room" looks like the old "double 11" command center. The corridor is lined with fruit snacks. Next to the wall is a small washbasin lined with toothbrushes, toothpaste, shampoo and body wash. The camp beds are all in place.

However, this "war room" is not the usual crowd, thousands of square meters of office space, only a few dozen people. Everyone worked feverishly like a stock exchange; everyone sat at a separate desk at dinner, facing the same direction, keeping their heads down. It's about efficiency and safety.

Since the promotion of Health Code in Zhejiang, more and more provinces and cities came to our door. On the evening of Valentine's Day, we were testing the health code in Zhejiang Province. Suddenly, we were informed that the health code in Sichuan Province would be launched the next day. Meanwhile, we had to develop a national health code system..

Every time the wall thinks it's over after this job, it turns out it's gone from a blitz to a protracted war.

Administration students originally wanted to add a few camp beds, but found that the originally prepared bed did not move much. A ask just know, in order to rush for time, almost all people are not sleep, even some people do two days in a row, and then go home to wash sleep again.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On Feb. 18, Zhou Jiangyong, the party secretary of Hangzhou, came to the war room to pay his respects, which was filled with toothpaste, toothbrush, face towel and Washbasin.

The most common use was for towels prepared in advance by the administration. I can't hold it any longer. Warm the towel with hot water and apply it to your eyes.

"To combat the epidemic, we need to have a real-time map of the local situation. Health, suspected and confirmed cases will be reported and updated by the public. This can not be done by paper, but by digital means. Yi Zhi, project manager of healthcode and a senior project management expert at Alipay, said the paper route is an island, and can only prove your current state, but the healthcode is dynamic, according to standards set by the government, users in the health of the card declaration information, will each receive a code, this code with their daily status submission, changes in the area, health, and other factors, will change accordingly. For example, according to Hangzhou rules, local yellow code users will switch to Green Code after seven consecutive days of home isolation and healthy punching, without any symptoms of discomfort. "This dynamic management has greatly reduced the government's war costs. ".

A lot of collaborative demand, information exchange allows the "war room" to be filled with 24-hour teleconferencing, video calls, pin calls, and all cell phones and computers are charged at all times.

Talking too much, the mask is easy to get wet, people have to be in front of the computer, mobile phones, while trying to hold down the impulse to take off the mask.

Most of the meeting times displayed on the top right of your computer are more than two hours, as hundreds of colleagues who could not return to their offices are working in the cloud in their homes. Various conference calls, from time to time came the baby crow dog bark chicken call pigs.

For the people's livelihood section, even if he did win, his colleagues knew he was on the phone -- as if the barking of his next door neighbor were ringing off the hook. I haven't been downstairs in over 20 days, and the three dogs are going crazy.

Ying Si, a business development expert at Alipay, has been holed up in his parents'home since he returned to Wuhan with his wife on January 20. The 10 month old prefers to play in the living room when awake, ducking out to the balcony to work; when he needs quiet while he sleeps, he is shunted to the kitchen farthest from the bedroom to make phone calls.

In the middle of a job at Split Second, his phone's alarm clock would suddenly ring: It was time for all kinds of apps to steal food. The success rate is not high, starting from the third day of the New Year, the whole family from Three Meals a Day to two meals. Even more alarming was the fact that they lived in a neighborhood of nearly 100 suspected and confirmed patients, with the nearest confirmed patient living directly across the street from them.

At noon on February 17th, the meeting was in full swing until the leaders of the family pulled out their earphones and pressed mute -- 'you know food isn't easy? There are only two cabbages at home, six cabbages, and do not think of a way to quickly rob some more! "

The product manager in the closet

Bo-yeon started switching into work mode on the fourth day of the Lunar New Year. She is a senior product expert at alipay. On her way home, she saw that due to the impact of the epidemic, checkpoints were set up at high-speed tollbooths all over the country. The staff were wearing masks, goggles and protective clothing, vehicle-to-vehicle registration of Health and movement data of migrants.

Product managers stuck in a traffic jam on their way home will meet and talk about the possibility of turning registration into an online form, which would be much more efficient.

On the fourth day of the Lunar New Year, colleagues scattered across the country began to collaborate remotely online, quickly building a simple model: The EHEALTH card. With the health card, you can fill in the alipay on the implementation, do not need to "human flesh" under-line registration.

Back home remote collaboration, each has their own style of painting.

Someone's home is in the northwest mountains, and there's no signal in the house, only in the yard. In the frost wind, in order not to be an ice sculpture, every day up must first firewood, and then the fire, burning up, before the boot.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Some rural power supply instability, the old house suddenly power failure, the computer soon out of power, hard-core GRANDPA borrowed a neighbor generator. The old man is very proud: granddaughter to discuss the work, you do not understand.

Someone Home Network instability, holding a computer down the room, found the best signal in the closet, so did not hesitate to set up a computer desk in the closet.

On the seventh day of the Lunar New Year, the health card finished product design Demo.

The 17th day of the first lunar month, the whole country resume work soon, the First Edition Health Card product completes.

At that time, Hangzhou Health Code has been issued a few days, the National Netizen borrow a use in the network was played into a trick.

On February 10, the day the first version of the health card product was completed, Poyan received the assignment from all in to launch Zhejiang Health Code. She replied to the supervisor, product classmates are ready.
